{"id":45,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":45,"title":"Chapter 42: The Signs of Christ’s Crucifixion","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 42","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 42"],["h1","The Signs of Christ’s Crucifixion"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p3"},"Thirty-three years had passed since the people had seen the signs of Jesus Christ’s birth."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.2"},"3 Nephi 8:2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p5"},"They now watched for the sign of his death: three days of darkness."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.3"},"3 Nephi 8:3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p7"},"Some did not believe that the sign would come. They argued with those who did believe."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.4"},"3 Nephi 8:4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p9"},"One day a fierce storm came. There was a terrible wind."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.5-6"},"3 Nephi 8:5–6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p11"},"Lightning flashed, and thunder shook the whole earth."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.6-7"},"3 Nephi 8:6–7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p13"},"The city of Zarahemla caught on fire. The city of Moroni sank into the sea. The city of Moronihah was buried."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.8-10"},"3 Nephi 8:8–10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p15"},"An earthquake shook the whole earth. Highways were broken up, and buildings crumbled. Many cities were destroyed, and many people were killed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.12-15"},"3 Nephi 8:12–15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p17"},"The storm and the earthquake lasted about three hours."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.19"},"3 Nephi 8:19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p19"},"When the storm and earthquake stopped, thick darkness covered the land. There was no light anywhere. The people could even feel the darkness."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.19-20"},"3 Nephi 8:19–20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p21"},"The darkness lasted for three days. Candles would not burn, and the people could not see the sun, moon, or stars."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.21-23"},"3 Nephi 8:21–23"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p23"},"The people cried because of the darkness, destruction, and death. They were sorry they had not repented of their sins."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/8.23-25"},"3 Nephi 8:23–25"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p25"},"Then the people heard the voice of Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/9.1,15"},"3 Nephi 9:1, 15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p27"},"Jesus told them about the terrible destruction in the land. He said that the most wicked people had been killed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/9.12-13"},"3 Nephi 9:12–13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p29"},"He said that those who had not been killed needed to repent. If they did and came unto him, he would bless them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/9.13-14"},"3 Nephi 9:13–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p31"},"The people were so amazed after hearing the voice that they stopped crying. Everything was silent for many hours."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/10.1-2"},"3 Nephi 10:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p33"},"Then Jesus spoke again, saying he had often tried to help the people. If they would repent now, they could still return to him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/10.3-6"},"3 Nephi 10:3–6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_045_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p35"},"After three days the darkness left. The people rejoiced and joyfully thanked the Lord."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-42-the-signs-of-christs-crucifixion.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/10.9-10"},"3 Nephi 10:9–10"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
